# Cursor Agent Rules — Planet Motors / Planet Ultra
# These rules apply to every task in this repo. Read them before starting any work.

---

## Identity & Voice

You are working on a real dealership storefront for Planet Motors in Richmond Hill, Ontario.
Every word a customer reads — titles, descriptions, metadata, alt text, schema fields — must
sound like it was written by a knowledgeable, trustworthy human who knows cars and respects
the buyer's time. It must never read like it was generated by an AI.

---

## SEO Writing Rules

### Metadata

- Title tags: lead with the strongest keyword signal, then brand — write for click-through, not
  keyword density. Max 60 characters.
  Good: `2021 Honda Civic LX Sedan — Planet Motors Richmond Hill`
  Bad:  `Honda Civic LX 2021 Used Car Inventory Dealership Ontario`

- Meta descriptions: one or two genuine sentences. Mention one real, specific detail about the
  page content. End with a soft, natural CTA. Max 155 characters. No keyword stuffing.
  Good: `Low-mileage 2021 Civic with clean Carfax and original floor mats. Book a test drive today.`
  Bad:  `Find the best used Honda Civic LX deals at Planet Motors. Browse inventory. Contact us today.`

- Every page's title and description must be unique. Never generate the same description twice
  for two different pages.

### On-Page Copy

- Write at a Grade 9 reading level. Plain words beat impressive words.
- Vary sentence length deliberately. Short sentences land a point. Longer ones can carry nuance
  and give the reader something to follow.
- Use contractions naturally: we're, you'll, it's, that's. Stiff formal constructions signal AI.
- Use second person ("you", "your") for customer-facing copy. Never "one" or "the customer".
- Lead with the most useful information. Never bury the key fact at the end.

### Banned Phrases — Never Use These

The following phrases are AI tells. Never use them in any copy, metadata, alt text, or schema:

  dive into / delve into / let's explore / it's worth noting / needless to say
  seamless / robust / cutting-edge / game-changer / revolutionize / leverage (as a verb)
  in today's world / in today's digital age / in the ever-evolving landscape
  a testament to / look no further / your one-stop shop / we pride ourselves
  Welcome to [Brand] (never open a page with this)
  Don't hesitate to contact us (passive and weak — use "Talk to us" or "Get in touch")

### Headlines (H1, H2, H3)

- H1 must match the primary search intent of the page — not just echo the title tag.
- H2s should guide the reader through the page logically, like a table of contents a human
  would write.
- Never keyword-stuff a headline. One clear idea per heading.

---

## Vehicle Copy Rules (VDP / Inventory Cards)

- Always lead with year, make, model, and one honest standout detail:
  Good: `This 2020 Toyota RAV4 XLE came in as a one-owner trade with 48,000 km and no accidents.`
  Bad:  `Browse our selection of quality pre-owned Toyota RAV4 vehicles at competitive prices.`

- Mention condition signals honestly: clean Carfax, one owner, original tires, recent service —
  whatever is true and verifiable.
- If a detail is unknown, omit it. Never invent or assume vehicle facts.
- Alt text on vehicle images must be descriptive and specific:
  Good: `Front three-quarter view of a 2020 white Toyota RAV4 XLE at Planet Motors`
  Bad:  `Used SUV for sale` or `vehicle-image`

---

## Structured Data (JSON-LD) Writing Rules

- description fields in schema must be full, readable English sentences — not keyword strings.
- name fields must reflect real page/entity names — not SEO keyword phrases.
- Do not fabricate schema values. If a value is unknown or variable, omit the field rather than
  use a placeholder.

---

## General Agent Behavior

- Do not generate lorem ipsum or placeholder copy. Write real, usable draft copy every time.
  If you don't have enough information to write real copy, ask for the missing detail rather
  than filling in with generic text.
- Do not pad. Say what needs to be said and stop.
- Do not open any customer-facing page or component with "Welcome to Planet Motors".
- When writing any metadata, always check: would a real person click on this? If the answer
  is no, rewrite it.
- Preserve A1 route policy, A2 data boundaries, and A3 UI structure. A4 owns performance,
  SEO, media, and metadata only.
